"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"![](https://images.mirror-media.xyz/publication-images/QtuqIhEt3Pmw6gC1CKlMT.png?height=1674&width=3200)\\n\\n*We‚Äôre launching a series of workshops for DeFi creators*\\n\\n**Dear SuSy community!**\\n\\nWe are excited to introduce a series of development workshops called CoDeFi, where you can learn how to build DeFi applications and protocols with us!\\n\\nGet ready to dive deep into technological nuance and advanced topics: we‚Äôre happy to share our expertise in protocol building, coding smart contracts, designing product architecture while using a variety of dev tools and approaches.\\n\\nüë®‚ÄçüíªWho are we? The SuSy core development team.\\n\\nüí≠Why do we do this? We‚Äôve been out there for a long time, working on different projects: developed DeFi products with a 10-digit market cap, created scalable cross-chain oracle solutions and highly-reliable concurrency systems, and worked on maintenance of L1 protocols‚Äô infrastructure. We want to share our experience and skills to bring a better, more scalable and sustainable world of DeFi development.\\n\\n‚ö°Ô∏èThe first edition is dedicated to multisig applications on the Solana blockchain.\\n\\nOther topics will cover:\\n\\n* Creating a multisig contract on Solana\\n* Cross-chain bridges: EVM & non-EVM\\n* Learning Rust by building DeFi applications\\n* Deployment of an Ethereum smart contract in three minutes\\n* ‚ÄúRelay token‚Äù concept: how it works\\n* Testing of smart contracts\\n\\nA further lineup of events is to be announced! Follow our Twitter to stay tuned.\\n\\nOn every cycle of workshops, we‚Äôll be rewarding with $GTON all those most involved in upgrading their development skills and coding achievements. After each workshop, we‚Äôll be sharing a test to check what you‚Äôve learned and distribute rewards.\\n\\nJoin us next Wednesday to participate in the first workshop ‚ÄúMultisig on Solana. Exploring existing solutions.‚Äù For a detailed agenda, go [here](https://www.